******
[2]
Date: Mon 16 Feb 2004
Source: The Nation [edited]
<http://www.nationmultimedia.com/home/2004/02/17/latest%20news/Hundreds-of-storks-have-died-of-bird-flu-93732.html>


Hundreds of storks at 2 bird sanctuaries outside Bangkok have died of
the bird flu that has struck Asia's poultry farms, but there are no
plans to destroy the wildlife in the area, officials said Tuesday [10
Feb 2004].

Some 500 openbill storks were found dead in Lat Krabang district and
300 birds had died at the Bueng Boraphet wetland in Nakhon Sawan
province since 27 Jan 2004, said Minister of Natural Resources and
Environment Prapat Panyachatraksa on Tuesday [10 Feb 2004].

Laboratory tests found 30 percent to 40 percent of the dead storks,
which are migratory birds, were infected with bird flu virus, he said.

--
