[This would suggest that this is an ongoing problem that fell below
the radar for a few years, and returned with excited headlines of
"thousands" of deaths. However I can find no ProMED reports on
openbill storks in Thailand in 2004 and 2005. Under the circumstances
I think we can accept Dr Praphat's original statement that these
migratory storks got infected when they arrived in Thailand. -
Mod.MHJ]
